# Frontend: Vite + Electron only

Do not edit the legacy static HTML frontend. All UI features, fixes, and layout changes belong in the desktop app.

## Do not edit

- `freecad-studio/frontend/**` — static HTML, CSS, and JS served by the FastAPI backend
- Do not add features, fix UI bugs, or refactor in those files even if the backend still serves them

## Edit instead

- `freecad-studio-desktop/src/**` — React UI (Vite)
- `freecad-studio-desktop/electron/**` — Electron main/preload/process
- `freecad-studio-desktop/vite.config.ts`, `tsconfig*.json` — Vite/Electron build config

## Vite shell only

- `freecad-studio-desktop/index.html` is the Vite entry shell (`#root` + module script). Prefer `src/` components for UI. Only touch `index.html` for fonts, meta tags, or Vite entry requirements — not for app layout or behavior.

## Backend

- API and server logic stay in `freecad-studio/backend/**`. Do not mirror or duplicate UI work in the static frontend.
